Routers and switches are essential devices that help transfer data efficiently between computers and networks. Though they both forward data, 
they operate at different layers of the OSI model and serve different purposes.

ğŸ‘‰ Switch: The Local Traffic Controller

A Switch connects multiple devices (computers, printers, servers) within the same local area network (LAN).
It works at the Data Link Layer (Layer 2) of the OSI model and uses MAC addresses to identify where to send data frames.

